{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775876094659,"sessionID":"ses_28589fcd5ffeZww7Fu5O5YeCAx","part":{"id":"prt_d7a76bab1001SUuOukWcpoc57h","messageID":"msg_d7a7691f6001u3lfVmFspk7K6h","sessionID":"ses_28589fcd5ffeZww7Fu5O5YeCAx","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-79af08de485b45ae857bd6da052e2952","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-024/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-024/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Delta Spec: AR-024 — DockerService 封装\n2: \n3: **Module:** `cmd/cli`  \n4: **Language:** Python  \n5: **Size:** M\n6: \n7: ---\n8: \n9: ## Overview\n10: \n11: Encapsulates Docker SDK operations for container image lifecycle management: availability checking, building, information retrieval, registry push, and removal. The `DockerService` class provides a clean abstraction layer over the `docker` Python SDK, enabling CLI commands (`build`, `publish`) to manage container images without direct SDK coupling.\n12: \n13: ---\n14: \n15: ## GIVEN/WHEN/THEN Scenarios\n16: \n17: ### Requirement: Docker client lazy initialization\n18: \n19: The system SHALL lazily initialize the Docker client via `docker.from_env()` on first use, caching the client for subsequent operations.\n20: \n21: #### Scenario: Client deferred until first operation\n22: \n23: - **GIVEN** a `DockerService` instance is constructed with `verbose=False`\n24: - **WHEN** no Docker operations have been invoked yet\n25: - **THEN** the internal `_client` field SHALL be `None`\n26: \n27: #### Scenario: Client initialized on first `_get_client` call\n28: \n29: - **GIVEN** `_client` is `None`\n30: - **WHEN** `_get_client()` is called\n31: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n32:   - Import the `docker` module lazily\n33:   - Call `docker.from_env()` to obtain a client\n34:   - Store the result in `self._client`\n35:   - Return the client object\n36: \n37: #### Scenario: Client reused on subsequent calls\n38: \n39: - **GIVEN** `_client` has been initialized previously\n40: - **WHEN** `_get_client()` is called again\n41: - **THEN** the system SHALL return the cached `self._client` without re-initializing\n42: \n43: ---\n44: \n45: ### Requirement: Docker availability check\n46: \n47: The system SHALL provide `check_docker_available()` to verify Docker daemon connectivity.\n48: \n49: #### Scenario: Docker daemon running and responsive\n50: \n51: - **GIVEN** the Docker daemon is running and the socket is accessible\n52: - **WHEN** `check_docker_available()` is called\n53: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n54:   - Import `docker` and call `docker.from_env()`\n55:   - Invoke `client.ping()`\n56:   - Return `True`\n57: \n58: #### Scenario: Docker daemon stopped or unreachable\n59: \n60: - **GIVEN** the Docker daemon is stopped or the socket is inaccessible\n61: - **WHEN** `check_docker_available()` is called\n62: - **THEN** the system SHALL catch any exception and return `False`\n63: \n64: ---\n65: \n66: ### Requirement: Image building\n67: \n68: The system SHALL build container images from a Dockerfile with optional build arguments and verbose log streaming.\n69: \n70: #### Scenario: Build image with default parameters\n71: \n72: - **GIVEN** a valid `dockerfile_path`, `context_path`, and `image_name`\n73: - **WHEN** `build_image()` is called with default `tag=\"latest\"` and `build_args=None`\n74: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n75:   - Call `client.images.build(path=context_path, dockerfile=dockerfile_path, tag=\"{image_name}:latest\")`\n76:   - Record `build_time` as elapsed seconds from start to completion\n77:   - Return `{\"image_name\", \"image_id\", \"image_size\", \"build_time\", \"tag\"}`\n78: \n79: #### Scenario: Build image with custom tag\n80: \n81: - **GIVEN** `tag=\"v1.2.3\"` is passed to `build_image()`\n82: - **WHEN** the build runs\n83: - **THEN** the full tag SHALL be `{image_name}:v1.2.3`\n84: \n85: #### Scenario: Build image with proxy build arguments\n86: \n87: - **GIVEN** `build_args={\"HTTP_PROXY\": \"http://proxy.example.com:8080\", \"NO_PROXY\": \"localhost\"}`\n88: - **WHEN** `build_image()` is invoked\n89: - **THEN** the system SHALL pass `buildargs` to `client.images.build()` so Docker receives the proxy settings\n90: \n91: #### Scenario: Verbose build log streaming\n92: \n93: - **GIVEN** `verbose=True` is passed to `build_image()`\n94: - **WHEN** the build runs\n95: - **THEN** the system SHALL iterate over `build_logs` and print each `log[\"stream\"]` line (stripped) to stdout\n96: \n97: #### Scenario: Build failure with verbose output\n98: \n99: - **GIVEN** `build_image()` encounters an exception during the build\n100: - **WHEN** `verbose=True`\n101: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n102:   - Record elapsed time as `build_time`\n103:   - Print `\"Build failed after {build_time:.1f}s: {e}\"` to stdout\n104:   - Raise the exception\n105: \n106: ---\n107: \n108: ### Requirement: Image information retrieval\n109: \n110: The system SHALL retrieve metadata (ID, size) for a built or pulled image.\n111: \n112: #### Scenario: Get info for existing image with tag\n113: \n114: - **GIVEN** image `{image_name}:{tag}` exists locally\n115: - **WHEN** `get_image_info(image_name, tag)` is called\n116: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n117:   - Call `client.images.get(\"{image_name}:{tag}\")`\n118:   - Extract `image.id` and `image.attrs.get(\"Size\", 0)`\n119:   - Format size via `_format_size()`\n120:   - Return `{\"image_id\", \"image_size\"}`\n121: \n122: #### Scenario: Get info with default tag\n123: \n124: - **GIVEN** `get_image_info(image_name)` is called without `tag`\n125: - **WHEN** the method runs\n126: - **THEN** the system SHALL use `tag=\"latest\"` as the default\n127: \n128: #### Scenario: Image not found\n129: \n130: - **GIVEN** the specified image does not exist locally\n131: - **WHEN** `get_image_info()` is called\n132: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n133:   - Catch the Docker SDK exception\n134:   - If `self.verbose=True`, print `\"Error getting image info: {e}\"` to stdout\n135:   - Re-raise the exception\n136: \n137: ---\n138: \n139: ### Requirement: Image size formatting\n140: \n141: The system SHALL format byte counts as human-readable strings.\n142: \n143: #### Scenario: Bytes under 1 KB\n144: \n145: - **GIVEN** `size_bytes < 1024`\n146: - **WHEN** `_format_size(size_bytes)` is called\n147: - **THEN** the result SHALL be `\"size_bytes B\"` (e.g., `\"512 B\"`)\n148: \n149: #### Scenario: Kilobytes (1 KB to 1 MB)\n150: \n151: - **GIVEN** `1024 <= size_bytes < 1024 * 1024`\n152: - **WHEN** `_format_size(size_bytes)` runs\n153: - **THEN** the result SHALL be `\"size_bytes / 1024:.1f KB\"` (e.g., `\"256.0 KB\"`)\n154: \n155: #### Scenario: Megabytes (1 MB to 1 GB)\n156: \n157: - **GIVEN** `1024 * 1024 <= size_bytes < 1024 * 1024 * 1024`\n158: - **WHEN** `_format_size(size_bytes)` runs\n159: - **THEN** the result SHALL be `\"size_bytes / (1024 * 1024):.1f MB\"` (e.g., `\"64.0 MB\"`)\n160: \n161: #### Scenario: Gigabytes (>= 1 GB)\n162: \n163: - **GIVEN** `size_bytes >= 1024 * 1024 * 1024`\n164: - **WHEN** `_format_size(size_bytes)` runs\n165: - **THEN** the result SHALL be `\"size_bytes / (1024 * 1024 * 1024):.1f GB\"` (e.g., `\"2.5 GB\"`)\n166: \n167: ---\n168: \n169: ### Requirement: Image push to registry\n170: \n171: The system SHALL push images to a container registry with optional authentication.\n172: \n173: #### Scenario: Push without registry URL\n174: \n175: - **GIVEN** `registry_url` is `None` or empty\n176: - **WHEN** `push_image(image_name)` is called\n177: - **THEN** the system SHALL push to `image_name` directly (assumes local registry or daemon-inferred target)\n178: \n179: #### Scenario: Push with registry URL\n180: \n181: - **GIVEN** `registry_url=\"registry.example.com\"`\n182: - **WHEN** `push_image(image_name, registry_url)` runs\n183: - **THEN** the full image name SHALL be `\"registry.example.com/{image_name}\"`\n184: \n185: #### Scenario: Push with authentication\n186: \n187: - **GIVEN** `username=\"user\"`, `password=\"pass\"`, and `registry_url` are all provided\n188: - **WHEN** `push_image()` is called\n189: - **THEN** the system SHALL call `client.login(username=username, password=password, registry=registry_url)` before pushing\n190: \n191: #### Scenario: Push timing measurement\n192: \n193: - **GIVEN** a push operation completes\n194: - **WHEN** `push_image()` returns\n195: - **THEN** the system SHALL return `{\"pushed_image\": full_image_name, \"push_time\": elapsed_seconds}`\n196: \n197: ---\n198: \n199: ### Requirement: Image removal\n200: \n201: The system SHALL remove local images with graceful failure handling.\n202: \n203: #### Scenario: Successful image removal\n204: \n205: - **GIVEN** image `image_name` exists locally and is not in use\n206: - **WHEN** `remove_image(image_name)` is called\n207: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n208:   - Call `client.images.remove(image_name)`\n209:   - Return `True`\n210: \n211: #### Scenario: Removal failure (image in use or not found)\n212: \n213: - **GIVEN** the image cannot be removed (e.g., in use by a container, or does not exist)\n214: - **WHEN** `remove_image(image_name)` raises an exception\n215: - **THEN** the system SHALL catch the exception and return `False`\n216: \n217: ---\n218: \n219: ### Requirement: Legacy build wrapper\n220: \n221: The system SHALL provide `build_image_legacy()` for backward compatibility with workspace/metadata-based builds.\n222: \n223: #### Scenario: Legacy build with metadata defaults\n224: \n225: - **GIVEN** `workspace_path`, `metadata: AgentMetadata`\n226: - **WHEN** `build_image_legacy(workspace_path, metadata)` is called\n227: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n228:   - Use `dockerfile_path = workspace_path / \"Dockerfile\"`\n229:   - Use `context_path = workspace_path`\n230:   - Use `image_name = metadata.agent_name`\n231:   - Use `tag = metadata.version or \"latest\"`\n232:   - Use `build_args = None`\n233:   - Call `build_image()` with the above parameters\n234: \n235: #### Scenario: Legacy build with explicit tag override\n236: \n237: - **GIVEN** `tag=\"v2.0.0\"` is passed to `build_image_legacy()`\n238: - **WHEN** the build executes\n239: - **THEN** the tag SHALL be `\"v2.0.0\"` (overrides `metadata.version`)\n240: \n241: #### Scenario: Legacy build inherits verbose setting\n242: \n243: - **GIVEN** `DockerService` was constructed with `verbose=True`\n244: - **WHEN** `build_image_legacy()` is called without explicit `verbose`\n245: - **THEN** the `verbose` argument passed to `build_image()` SHALL be `self.verbose`\n246: \n247: ---\n248: \n249: ### Requirement: Constructor initialization\n250: \n251: The system SHALL initialize `DockerService` with a verbose flag and uninitialized client.\n252: \n253: #### Scenario: Constructor with verbose flag\n254: \n255: - **GIVEN** `DockerService(verbose=True)` is called\n256: - **WHEN** the instance is created\n257: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n258:   - Store `self.verbose = True`\n259:   - Initialize `self._client = None`\n260: \n261: #### Scenario: Constructor default verbose\n262: \n263: - **GIVEN** `DockerService()` is called without arguments\n264: - **WHEN** the instance is created\n265: - **THEN** `self.verbose` SHALL default to `False`\n266: \n267: ---\n268: \n269: ## Constants Summary\n270: \n271: | Constant | Value | File | Purpose |\n272: |----------|-------|------|---------|\n273: | Default tag | `\"latest\"` | `docker_service.py` | Default image tag for builds and info retrieval |\n274: | Size thresholds | `1024`, `1024*1024`, `1024*1024*1024` | `docker_service.py` | Thresholds for size formatting (KB, MB, GB) |\n275: \n276: ---\n277: \n278: ## Dependencies Summary\n279: \n280: | Package | Version | Purpose |\n281: |---------|---------|---------|\n282: | `docker` | `>=6.0.0` | Docker SDK for Python (client API) |\n283: | `time` | stdlib | Build/push timing measurement |\n284: | `pathlib.Path` | stdlib | Dockerfile and context path handling |\n285: | `typing` | stdlib | Type annotations (`Optional`, `Dict`, `Any`) |\n286: \n287: ---\n288: \n289: ## File Changes Summary\n290: \n291: | File | Action | Description |\n292: |------|--------|-------------|\n293: | `agentcube/services/docker_service.py` | **existing** | Core DockerService implementation |\n294: | `agentcube/runtime/build_runtime.py` | uses | Consumes `DockerService.build_image()` for local builds |\n295: | `agentcube/runtime/publish_runtime.py` | uses | Consumes `DockerService.push_image()` for registry push |\n296: \n297: ---\n298: \n299: ## References\n300: \n301: - Docker SDK for Python: https://docker-py.readthedocs.io/\n302: - `cli-toolkit/design.md`: DockerService API signature and field descriptions\n303: - `cli-toolkit/spec.md`: Docker integration requirement scenarios\n304: \n305: ---\n306: \n307: ## Validation Checklist\n308: \n309: - [ ] `DockerService.__init__` stores `verbose` and initializes `_client=None`\n310: - [ ] `_get_client()` lazy-initializes via `docker.from_env()` and caches result\n311: - [ ] `check_docker_available()` returns `True` when daemon responds to ping\n312: - [ ] `check_docker_available()` returns `False` on any exception\n313: - [ ] `build_image()` calls `client.images.build()` with correct parameters\n314: - [ ] `build_image()` returns `{image_name, image_id, image_size, build_time, tag}`\n315: - [ ] `build_image()` streams logs when `verbose=True`\n316: - [ ] `build_image()` prints failure timing when verbose and exception occurs\n317: - [ ] `build_image()` supports `build_args` for proxy configuration\n318: - [ ] `get_image_info()` returns `{image_id, image_size}` for existing image\n319: - [ ] `get_image_info()` uses `tag=\"latest\"` as default\n320: - [ ] `get_image_info()` prints error and re-raises when `verbose=True`\n321: - [ ] `_format_size()` formats bytes as B/KB/MB/GB correctly\n322: - [ ] `push_image()` constructs full image name with registry URL\n323: - [ ] `push_image()` calls `client.login()` when credentials provided\n324: - [ ] `push_image()` returns `{pushed_image, push_time}`\n325: - [ ] `remove_image()` returns `True` on success, `False` on failure\n326: - [ ] `build_image_legacy()` wraps `build_image()` with workspace/metadata defaults\n327: - [ ] `build_image_legacy()` uses `metadata.version or \"latest\"` as tag\n328: - [ ] `build_image_legacy()` inherits `self.verbose` setting\n\n(End of file - total 328 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Delta Spec: AR-024 — DockerService 封装\n\n**Module:** `cmd/cli`  \n**Language:** Python  \n**Size:** M\n\n---\n\n## Overview\n\nEncapsulates Docker SDK operations for container image lifecycle management: availability checking, building, information retrieval, registry push, and removal. The `DockerService` class provides a clean abstraction layer over the `docker` Python SDK, enabling CLI commands (`build`, `publish`) to manage container images without direct SDK coupling.\n\n---\n\n## GIVEN/WHEN/THEN Scenarios\n\n### Requirement: Docker client lazy initialization\n\nThe system SHALL lazily initialize the Docker client via `docker.from_env()` on first use, caching the client for subsequent operations.\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-024/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775876094650,"end":1775876094657}}}}
