{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775876166898,"sessionID":"ses_28589fcd5ffeZww7Fu5O5YeCAx","part":{"id":"prt_d7a77d4880018ZhAllTscCAZ96","messageID":"msg_d7a76baf4001pK1ItqlP8PHNtw","sessionID":"ses_28589fcd5ffeZww7Fu5O5YeCAx","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_tool-4fedca1d4bb34341a9290e18fd659f05","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-024/tasks.md","content":"# AR-024 — DockerService 封装 Tasks\n\n## Metadata\n\n| Item | Value |\n|------|-------|\n| AR | AR-024 — DockerService 封装 |\n| Module | `cmd/cli` |\n| Language | Python |\n| Size | M |\n| Design | [Stage ST-3 completed] |\n\n---\n\n## Task Checklist\n\n### Phase 1: Core Implementation (ST-1)\n\n- [x] **T1.1**: Implement `DockerService.__init__` with verbose flag and `_client=None`\n  - Purpose: Constructor initializes verbose flag and lazy client placeholder\n  - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/docker_service.py:9-11`\n  - Verification: `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_docker_service.py::TestDockerServiceInit -v`\n\n- [x] **T1.2**: Implement `_get_client()` lazy-loading method\n  - Purpose: Lazy import docker SDK and cache client instance\n  - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/docker_service.py:13-17`\n  - Verification: `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_docker_service.py::TestCheckDockerAvailable -v`\n\n- [x] **T1.3**: Implement `check_docker_available()` method\n  - Purpose: Verify Docker daemon connectivity via ping\n  - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/docker_service.py:19-26`\n  - Verification: `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_docker_service.py::TestCheckDockerAvailable -v`\n\n- [x] **T1.4**: Implement `_format_size()` helper method\n  - Purpose: Convert byte count to human-readable B/KB/MB/GB string\n  - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/docker_service.py:28-36`\n  - Verification: `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_docker_service.py::TestFormatSize -v`\n\n### Phase 2: Image Operations (ST-2)\n\n- [x] **T2.1**: Implement `get_image_info()` method\n  - Purpose: Retrieve image metadata (ID, size) from Docker daemon\n  - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/docker_service.py:38-52`\n  - Verification: `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_docker_service.py::TestGetImageInfo -v`\n\n- [x] **T2.2**: Implement `build_image()` method\n  - Purpose: Build Docker image with optional build_args and verbose streaming\n  - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/docker_service.py:54-99`\n  - Verification: `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_docker_service.py::TestBuildImage -v`\n\n- [x] **T2.3**: Implement `build_image_legacy()` wrapper\n  - Purpose: Provide backward-compatible build with workspace/metadata defaults\n  - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/docker_service.py:101-115`\n  - Verification: `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_docker_service.py -k legacy -v`\n\n- [x] **T2.4**: Implement `push_image()` method\n  - Purpose: Push image to registry with optional authentication\n  - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/docker_service.py:117-144`\n  - Verification: `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_docker_service.py::TestPushImage -v`\n\n- [x] **T2.5**: Implement `remove_image()` method\n  - Purpose: Remove local image with graceful failure handling\n  - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/docker_service.py:146-152`\n  - Verification: `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_docker_service.py::TestRemoveImage -v`\n\n### Phase 3: Unit Tests (ST-3)\n\n- [x] **T3.1**: Write initialization tests\n  - Purpose: Verify constructor behavior with verbose flag\n  - File: `cmd/cli/tests/test_docker_service.py:9-16`\n  - Verification: `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_docker_service.py::TestDockerServiceInit -v`\n\n- [x] **T3.2**: Write Docker availability tests\n  - Purpose: Verify check_docker_available returns True/False correctly\n  - File: `cmd/cli/tests/test_docker_service.py:19-31`\n  - Verification: `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_docker_service.py::TestCheckDockerAvailable -v`\n\n- [x] **T3.3**: Write size formatting tests\n  - Purpose: Verify _format_size handles B/KB/MB/GB thresholds\n  - File: `cmd/cli/tests/test_docker_service.py:34-54`\n  - Verification: `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_docker_service.py::TestFormatSize -v`\n\n- [x] **T3.4**: Write get_image_info tests\n  - Purpose: Verify image metadata retrieval and error handling\n  - File: `cmd/cli/tests/test_docker_service.py:57-84`\n  - Verification: `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_docker_service.py::TestGetImageInfo -v`\n\n- [x] **T3.5**: Write build_image tests\n  - Purpose: Verify build with default/custom tag, build_args, verbose, failure\n  - File: `cmd/cli/tests/test_docker_service.py:87-180`\n  - Verification: `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_docker_service.py::TestBuildImage -v`\n\n- [x] **T3.6**: Write push_image tests\n  - Purpose: Verify push with registry URL, authentication\n  - File: `cmd/cli/tests/test_docker_service.py:183-228`\n  - Verification: `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_docker_service.py::TestPushImage -v`\n\n- [x] **T3.7**: Write remove_image tests\n  - Purpose: Verify removal success and graceful failure\n  - File: `cmd/cli/tests/test_docker_service.py:230-250`\n  - Verification: `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_docker_service.py::TestRemoveImage -v`\n\n### Phase 4: Integration Verification (ST-4)\n\n- [ ] **T4.1**: Verify DockerService integration with BuildRuntime\n  - Purpose: Ensure BuildRuntime correctly consumes DockerService.build_image()\n  - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/build_runtime.py`\n  - Verification: `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_build_runtime.py -v`\n\n- [ ] **T4.2**: Verify DockerService integration with PublishRuntime\n  - Purpose: Ensure PublishRuntime correctly consumes DockerService.push_image()\n  - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/publish_runtime.py`\n  - Verification: `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_publish_runtime.py -v`\n\n- [ ] **T4.3**: Verify __init__.py exports DockerService\n  - Purpose: Ensure DockerService is exported from services package\n  - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/__init__.py`\n  - Verification: `python -c \"from agentcube.services import DockerService; print('OK')\"`\n\n- [ ] **T4.4**: Run full test suite\n  - Purpose: Verify all tests pass together\n  - File: `cmd/cli/tests/test_docker_service.py`\n  - Verification: `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_docker_service.py -v`\n\n---\n\n## Task Dependencies\n\n```\nT1.1 (init) ──┬── T1.2 (_get_client)\n              │\n              ├── T1.3 (check_docker)\n              │\n              └── T1.4 (_format_size)\n\nT1.2 + T1.4 ──┬── T2.1 (get_image_info)\n              │\n              ├── T2.2 (build_image)\n              │        │\n              │        └── T2.3 (build_image_legacy)\n              │\n              ├── T2.4 (push_image)\n              │\n              └── T2.5 (remove_image)\n\nT2.1-T2.5 ────┬── T3.1-T3.7 (unit tests)\n              │\n              └── T4.1-T4.4 (integration)\n```\n\n---\n\n## Verification Commands\n\n| Task | Verification Command |\n|------|----------------------|\n| T1.1 | `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_docker_service.py::TestDockerServiceInit -v` |\n| T1.2 | `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_docker_service.py::TestCheckDockerAvailable::test_docker_available -v` |\n| T1.3 | `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_docker_service.py::TestCheckDockerAvailable -v` |\n| T1.4 | `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_docker_service.py::TestFormatSize -v` |\n| T2.1 | `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_docker_service.py::TestGetImageInfo -v` |\n| T2.2 | `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_docker_service.py::TestBuildImage -v` |\n| T2.3 | `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_docker_service.py -k legacy -v` |\n| T2.4 | `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_docker_service.py::TestPushImage -v` |\n| T2.5 | `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_docker_service.py::TestRemoveImage -v` |\n| T3.1-T3.7 | `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_docker_service.py -v` |\n| T4.1 | `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_build_runtime.py -v` |\n| T4.2 | `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_publish_runtime.py -v` |\n| T4.3 | `python -c \"from agentcube.services import DockerService\"` |\n| T4.4 | `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_docker_service.py -v` |\n\n---\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [x] `DockerService.__init__` stores `verbose` and initializes `_client=None`\n- [x] `_get_client()` lazy-initializes via `docker.from_env()` and caches result\n- [x] `check_docker_available()` returns `True` when daemon responds to ping\n- [x] `check_docker_available()` returns `False` on any exception\n- [x] `build_image()` calls `client.images.build()` with correct parameters\n- [x] `build_image()` returns `{image_name, image_id, image_size, build_time, tag}`\n- [x] `build_image()` streams logs when `verbose=True`\n- [x] `build_image()` prints failure timing when verbose and exception occurs\n- [x] `build_image()` supports `build_args` for proxy configuration\n- [x] `get_image_info()` returns `{image_id, image_size}` for existing image\n- [x] `get_image_info()` uses `tag=\"latest\"` as default\n- [x] `get_image_info()` prints error and re-raises when `verbose=True`\n- [x] `_format_size()` formats bytes as B/KB/MB/GB correctly\n- [x] `push_image()` constructs full image name with registry URL\n- [x] `push_image()` calls `client.login()` when credentials provided\n- [x] `push_image()` returns `{pushed_image, push_time}`\n- [x] `remove_image()` returns `True` on success, `False` on failure\n- [x] `build_image_legacy()` wraps `build_image()` with workspace/metadata defaults\n- [x] `build_image_legacy()` uses `metadata.version or \"latest\"` as tag\n- [x] `build_image_legacy()` inherits `self.verbose` setting\n- [ ] All integration tests with BuildRuntime/PublishRuntime pass\n- [ ] DockerService exported from services package\n\n---\n\n## File Changes Summary\n\n| File | Action | Lines | Description |\n|------|--------|-------|-------------|\n| `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/docker_service.py` | Modify | 152 | Core DockerService implementation |\n| `cmd/cli/tests/test_docker_service.py` | Modify | 251 | Unit tests for all DockerService methods |\n| `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/__init__.py` | Modify | - | Export DockerService |\n| `cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/build_runtime.py` | Uses | - | Consumes DockerService.build_image() |\n| `cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/publish_runtime.py` | Uses | - | Consumes DockerService.push_image() |\n\n---\n\n## Implementation Notes\n\n### Lazy Client Loading\n\nThe `_get_client()` method uses lazy initialization to avoid import errors at module load time if the docker SDK is unavailable. The client is cached in `_client` for reuse across multiple operations.\n\n### Size Formatting Thresholds\n\n| Threshold | Output Format |\n|-----------|---------------|\n| `< 1024` | `\"{n} B\"` |\n| `< 1024²` | `\"{n/1024:.1f} KB\"` |\n| `< 1024³` | `\"{n/1024²:.1f} MB\"` |\n| `>= 1024³` | `\"{n/1024³:.1f} GB\"` |\n\n### Verbose Build Streaming\n\nWhen `verbose=True`, build logs are streamed line-by-line:\n```python\nfor log in build_logs:\n    if \"stream\" in log:\n        print(log[\"stream\"].strip())\n```\n\n---\n\n## Implementation Timeline\n\n| Phase | Tasks | Status | Completion |\n|-------|-------|--------|------------|\n| Phase 1: Core Implementation | T1.1-T1.4 | Done | 100% |\n| Phase 2: Image Operations | T2.1-T2.5 | Done | 100% |\n| Phase 3: Unit Tests | T3.1-T3.7 | Done | 100% |\n| Phase 4: Integration | T4.1-T4.4 | Pending | 0% |\n\n**Total Progress: 75% Complete (15/20 tasks)**\n\n---\n\n## References\n\n- Design: `changes/AR-024/design.md`\n- Delta Spec: `changes/AR-024/delta-spec.md`\n- Docker SDK Python: https://docker-py.readthedocs.io/en/stable/\n- AR-021 — CLI build command (uses DockerService)\n- AR-022 — CLI publish command (uses DockerService.push_image)"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/cmd/cli/tests/test_docker_service.py":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/cmd/cli/agentcube/services/docker_service.py":[]},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian